<html class="home">
<head>
    <%- include("includes/head") %>
    <% headUrl = "https://info.chrispricemusic.net/music"%>
    <% headName = "Chris Price • Music & Media | Music" %>
    <title><%= headName %></title>

    <!-- SEO Meta -->
    <meta name="description" content="Original music, sound design, and multimedia content by Chris Price. Explore compositions, media projects, and creative collaborations.">
    <meta name="keywords" content="Chris Price, music composer, media producer, sound designer, audio, original music, film score, video, content creator">
    <meta name="author" content="Chris Price">
    

    <!-- Open Graph (Facebook, LinkedIn, Discord) -->
    <meta property="og:title" content="<%= headName %>">
    <meta property="og:description" content="Explore the work of Chris Price: composer, sound designer, and media creator. Hear original scores and view featured media projects.">
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://info.chrispricemusic.net/img/chris.jpg">
    <meta property="og:url" content="<%= headUrl %>">
    <meta property="og:type" content="website">

    <!-- Twitter Card -->
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="<%= headName %>">
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Music and multimedia content by Chris Price. Discover original compositions and sound design projects.">
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://info.chrispricemusic.net/img/chris.jpg">

    <link rel="canonical" href="<%= headUrl %>">
    <style>
    .card:hover {
        box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 123, 255, 0.6);
    }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <%- include("includes/header", {header: "music"}) %>
    </header>
    <main class="main">
        <div style="margin: 16px;">
            <br>
            <div style="
            background-image: url('/img/chris-2.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
            background-position: center;
            padding: 100px 20px;
            text-align: center;
            color: white;
            text-shadow: 0px 0px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
            ">
            <h1>Chris Price</h1>
            <br>
            <p>Composer & Music Educator</p>
            <br>
            <a href="/portfolio"><button>View Portfolio</button></a>
        </div>
            
            <br>
            <p>Hi, I'm Chris Price — a composer, educator, and all-around music nerd based in Spokane, Washington. I earned my music degree from Whitworth University, and ever since, I’ve been diving deeper into everything from jazz theory to ensemble writing to weird experimental textures. I love learning, and I’ve never really stopped.</p>
            <br>
            <p>
            My main instruments are piano and trombone, but I try to stay flexible — I’ve picked up a lot of others along the way. I’m heavily involved in my church community, and you can usually catch me playing with the Spokane Falls Community College Jazz Band and a few of its combos. Over the years I’ve played in musicals, at private events, and onstage at professional gigs across the region.
            </p>
            <br>
            <div style="text-align: center;">
                <a href="/commission"><button>Commission A New Piece</button></a>
            </div>
            <br>
            <div class="long-img-wrapper">
                <img src="/img/gems.jpg" alt="Boise Gems Drum and Bugle Corps.">
                <div class="img-caption">Boise Gems Drum & Bugle Corps 2024</div>
            </div>
            <br>
            <p>I’ve been lucky to write for ensembles across the country — one of the coolest partnerships has been with the Boise Gems Drum & Bugle Corps. Beyond writing, I also work hands-on with groups, helping with instrumental technique, visual performance, and student leadership. I love being part of the growth process.</p>
            <br>
            <h1>Publishing Website</h1>
            <br>
            <p>
            Alongside composing, I’m also a programmer. I’ve built a publishing website where I showcase not just my own music, but works by other composers too. If you write music and want to reach performers, check out the site and see if it's a good fit. My goal with <strong>chrispricemusic.net</strong> is to make a platform where composers feel seen, and musicians can easily find exactly what they need.
            </p>
            <br>
            <div style="text-align: center;">
                <a href="https://chrispricemusic.net" target="_blank"><button>Publishing Website</button></a>
            </div>
            <br>
            <% if(events.length > 0) { %>
            <h1>Upcoming Events</h1>
            <p>If you want to hear my music live, here's what's coming up!</p>
            <br>
            <% 
                const show_old = false; // default true
                const now = new Date();
                const FOUR_HOURS_MS = 4 * 60 * 60 * 1000;
            %>

                <% events.forEach(event => {
                    const eventTime = new Date(event.datetime);
                    const isOld = now - eventTime > FOUR_HOURS_MS;
                    if (show_old || !isOld) { 
                %>
                <% 
                    const eventDate = new Date(event.datetime);
                    const optionsWeekday = { weekday: 'long' };
                    const weekday = eventDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', optionsWeekday);
                    const mm = String(eventDate.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, '0');
                    const dd = String(eventDate.getDate()).padStart(2, '0');
                    const yyyy = eventDate.getFullYear();

                    let hours = eventDate.getHours();
                    const minutes = String(eventDate.getMinutes()).padStart(2, '0');
                    const ampm = hours >= 12 ? 'pm' : 'am';
                    hours = hours % 12;
                    hours = hours ? hours : 12; // 0 -> 12

                    const formattedDateTime = `${weekday} • ${mm}/${dd}/${yyyy} • ${hours}:${minutes} ${ampm}`;
                %>
                    <div class="card" style="cursor: pointer;" onclick="window.location.href='/event/<%= event.slug %>'">
                        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 3fr 1fr; column-gap: 8px;">
                            <div>
                                <h2><%= event.title %></h2>
                                <p><%= event.description.substring(0, 40) %>...</p>
                                <p style="color: rgb(195, 232, 241)"> <%= formattedDateTime %></p>
                                <p style="color: rgb(195, 232, 241)"><strong>Location:</strong> <%= event.location %></p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <img src="/img/<%= event.image %>" alt="" style="width: 100%; height: 112px; object-fit: cover;">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                <%  } 
                }) %>
                <br>
                <div style="text-align: center;">
                    <a href="/events"><button>All Events</button></a>
                </div>
            <% } %>

            <br>
            <h1>Lessons</h1>
            <br>
            <p>I genuinely believe success isn't about winning — it's about motion. If you’re moving toward your goals, you’re already doing the most important part. I’ve been playing and writing music for over a decade, and I love sharing what I’ve learned. If you're interested in lessons — whether you're just starting out or want to go deeper — hit the button below to learn more.</p>
            <br>
            <div style="text-align: center;">
                <a href="/lessons"><button>Lessons</button></a>
            </div>
            </p>
            <br>
            <br>
            <h2>Fun Quizzes!</h2>
            <br>
            <% if(quizzes.length > 0) { %>
                <% quizzes.forEach(quiz => { %>
                    <div class="card" onclick="location.href='/quiz/<%= quiz.slug %>'">
                        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 3fr 1fr; column-gap: 8px;">
                            <div>
                                <div>
                                    <h2><%= quiz.title %></h2>
                                    <p><%= quiz.description.substring(0, 80) %>...</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <div>
                                    <img src="<%= quiz.heroImage %>" alt="" style="width: 100%; height: 112px; object-fit: cover;">
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                <% }) %>
            <% } %>
            <br>
            <h1>Blog</h1>
            <br>
            <p>I write about music, creativity, education, and whatever’s inspiring me at the moment. Sometimes it's deep dives into composition techniques, other times it's stories from the road or thoughts on music education. If you’re curious about how I think — or just want some behind-the-scenes — the blog is where it lives.<br><br>My programming blogs are mixed in there as well!</p>
            <br>
            <div style="text-align: center;">
                <a href="/blog"><button>Read the Blog</button></a>
            </div>
            <br>
            <h2>Recent Posts</h2>
            <br>
            <% if(blogs.length > 0) { %>
                <% blogs.forEach(blog => { %>
                    <div class="card" onclick="location.href='/blog/<%= blog.slug %>'">
                        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 3fr 1fr; column-gap: 8px;">
                            <div>
                                <div>
                                    <h2><%= blog.title %></h2>
                                    <small><%= new Date(blog.created_at).toLocaleDateString() %></small>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <small>By <b><%= blog.author %></b></small>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <div>
                                    <img src="<%= blog.hero %>" alt="" style="width: 100%; height: 112px; object-fit: cover;">
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                <% }) %>
            <% } %>

        </div>
        
    </main>
    <footer>
        <%- include("includes/footer") %>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>